Package ohos.ivihardware.tbox.model

Interface TBoxPropertyCallback


  • public interface TBoxPropertyCallback
    A callback class pertaining to subscribing to a specified T-Box signal.

    This class provides the following callback methods:

    • onChangeSignal: called when the VSA layer normally returns a T-Box signal value. This callback passes you the T-Box signal value.
    • onErrorSignal: called when the VSA layer fails to return a T-Box signal value. This callback passes you the signal ID and error code for you to determine how to handle the error.
    Since:
    3
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Ivi.TBOX

    • Method Detail

      • onChangeSignal

        void onChangeSignal​(TBoxBuffInfo propInfo)
        Called when the VSA layer normally returns the specified T-Box signal value.

        Periodic subscription: When the VSA layer normally returns a T-Box signal value, TBoxManager checks whether the subscription period is reached. If it is reached, this callback is invoked to pass you the signal value for you to determine the subsequent operation. For example, if you have subscribed to a T-Box signal at an interval of 400 ms, this callback is invoked every 400 ms to report the signal value to you.

        Aperiodic subscription: When a T-Box signal value changes, this callback is invoked to report the signal value to you.

        Parameters:
        propInfo - Indicates the information about the T-Box signal value, including the signal ID and the byte array of signal values. You must use the data format defined by Protocol Buffers to parse the signal values.
        Since:
        3

      • onErrorSignal

        void onErrorSignal​(java.lang.String propertyId,
                   int errorCode)
        Called when the VSA layer fails to return the specified T-Box signal value.

        If the VSA layer fails to return the T-Box signal value, this callback is invoked to pass you the signal ID and error code for you to determine how to handle the error.

        Parameters:
        propertyId - Identifies the T-Box signal.
        errorCode - Indicates the error code of the failure to return the signal value. The value can be a parameter error or other errors.
        Since:
        3
